				<div class="postbody">
				Whats wrong with a .50 cal BMG bolt action rifle? How is an M-16 type gun less dangerous? You can't just go to a gun shop and buy a military type weapon without a permit, a clean criminal background and proof of citizenship. To buy an AR-15 (your M-16 type gun that is ok to buy, also considered an assault rifle) you need to have a background check and pass, and you need to prove you are a citizen of the U.S. To buy a military type weapon (machine guns etc) you need to have a permit and license from the BATF, pay a $200 tax and if the ATF wants, they can come to your home and invade your privacy and check to see what types of guns you have. Did you know its legal to buy and own a silencer?? All you need to do is fill out some paperwork with the ATF, get a CLEO to signoff for you, pay a $200 tax and wait a few months for the ATF to approve your application to own a silencer. Same for machine guns. People just seem to think that you can just go to a gun shop, throw money on the table and buy whatever you want. It doesn't work that way.<br />
