Don't know enough about this one to have much of an informed opinion either. My initial reaction is that while they certainly do a lot of good, they also do a lot of things that do not arise from their original mission, and interfere a hell of a lot in the free market. A better replacement system could certainly be devised, however I wouldn't be in such a hurry to axe the FDA until I see something more acceptable as a replacement. The libertarian argument is that they have no constitutional authority to exist, and they are right about that.
