I sincerely doubt you can find more than ten universities in this country that do not receive some level of government funding, Raviel.  Universities are not completely privatized by any means.  Even the Ivy League universities receive government funding.  Stating that the USA has the best universities in the world is also a misconception, as frankly Japan's universities blow ours away.  Foreigners come here in many cases not because the quality of our colleges and teaching is so mind blowingly spectacular, but because it is <span style="font-weight: bold">by far less expensive</span> than in their own country.
