That is contrary to a Japanese person I know who once told me that an undergrad degree from a Japanese university was nearly worthless.  Hence why so many come to the US to get a degree.  An American Bachelors degree &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;  Japanese one.
<br />

<br />
Getting back to the subsidy and university thing, all public universities are directly subsidized by state governments.  That would be why they are called public universities.  Even private ones get an assload of government funding.  As Flarestar touched on you would be lucky to find a university that did not get government funding one way or another.<br />
